                  <history>
                    <origin>
                      <origDate notBefore="1900" notAfter="1925"/>                    
                    </origin>
                    <provenance>According to the account on the manuscripts’ provenance given by Eugène Tisserant, this manuscript is among those
                      acquired by <persName role="owner" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4805Grebaut">Sylvain Grébaut</persName> in <date when="1925"/> with funds of
                      <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS14055SaintJ">Jean Saint</persName>. 
                      The manuscripts originated from Šawā (ʾAddis ʾAbabā, Dabra Libānos, Dabra Bǝrhān),
                      Goǧǧām (Dimā Giyorgis, Marṭula Māryām, Dabra Warq) and Bagemdǝr (Gondar, ʾAzazo Takla Hāymānot) and very few from Tǝgrāy.
                    </provenance>
                    <acquisition when="1928">The manuscript entered the library on <date>18 April 1928</date>.</acquisition>
                  </history>
